{"author":{"id":"cc8322a500b8739c77faac347808f6026d9ccb7880d0aaa7ad76754163cd7fdb"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1782568927,"nonce":"D1JMJnS6yIGzDJRl+8GIPEyF3Hg=","kind":"plan","title":"Slice 7 — MCP adapter Implementation Plan"},{"type":3,"timestamp":1782568927,"nonce":"aS19kjo8vs7f7EAuqZ7t9j4RSlc=","body":"# Slice 7 — MCP adapter Implementation Plan\n\n\u003e **For agentic workers:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:subagent-driven-development (recommended) or superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task. Steps use checkbox (`- [ ]`) syntax for tracking.\n\n**Goal:** Expose kref to non-shell agent hosts via a `kref mcp` stdio server — a thin MCP adapter over `internal/store` offering five curated tools (remember, recall, get, update, supersede).\n\n**Architecture:** New `internal/mcpserver` package builds an `mcp.Server` (official `github.com/modelcontextprotocol/go-sdk`) and registers tools as thin handlers over `internal/store` — the unchanged capability core. `cmd/kref` gains a `kref mcp` command that calls `mcpserver.Serve(ctx, dir, version)` (so only `mcpserver` imports the SDK). Each handler opens the store per call (matches the CLI's per-command lifecycle), calls one store capability, and returns a `CallToolResult`. Tool input schemas auto-derive from json-tagged param structs. Reference: spec §6 (\"slice 7 build decisions\").\n\n**Tech Stack:** Go, `github.com/modelcontextprotocol/go-sdk` (new dep, stable 1.x), `internal/store`, ginkgo/gomega, Taskfile.\n\n---\n\n## Conventions for every task\n\n- **TDD loop:** failing test → run-fail → implement → run-pass → `gofmt -w` → commit.\n- **Test runner:** prefix Go commands with `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto`. `internal/mcpserver` and `cmd/kref` suites need `KREF_GITLEAKS=$(pwd)/bin/gitleaks` (cmd/kref's existing suite does; mcpserver doesn't scan but use the same invocation). `task test`/`task lint` are canonical.\n- **Ignore LSP \"GOTOOLCHAIN=local / No packages found / undefined\" diagnostics** — stale noise.\n- **Do NOT run `git stash`.** Stage files by name. Every commit ends with:\n  `Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e`\n\n## Verified SDK API (against the 1.x source — do not deviate)\n\n- `mcp.NewServer(\u0026mcp.Implementation{Name, Version}, nil) *mcp.Server`\n- `mcp.AddTool[In, Out any](s *mcp.Server, t *mcp.Tool, h mcp.ToolHandlerFor[In, Out])` — derives the input JSON-Schema from `In`'s json tags.\n- `mcp.ToolHandlerFor[In, Out] = func(ctx, *mcp.CallToolRequest, In) (*mcp.CallToolResult, Out, error)`\n- `mcp.CallToolResult{Content []mcp.Content, IsError bool, StructuredContent any}`; `\u0026mcp.TextContent{Text: ...}` implements `mcp.Content`. Tool-level (user) errors → `IsError: true` + a `TextContent` (NOT a Go error, so the model sees it). Internal failures → return a Go error.\n- `srv.Run(ctx, \u0026mcp.StdioTransport{}) error` (production).\n- Tests: `mcp.NewInMemoryTransports() (clientT, serverT)`, `srv.Connect(ctx, serverT, nil) (*ServerSession, error)`, `mcp.NewClient(\u0026mcp.Implementation{Name}, nil)`, `client.Connect(ctx, clientT, nil) (*ClientSession, error)`, `cs.CallTool(ctx, \u0026mcp.CallToolParams{Name, Arguments map[string]any}) (*mcp.CallToolResult, error)`, `cs.Close()`, `ss.Wait()`.\n\n## File structure\n\n| File | Change | Responsibility |\n|------|--------|----------------|\n| `go.mod`, `go.sum` | modify | add `github.com/modelcontextprotocol/go-sdk` |\n| `internal/mcpserver/server.go` | create | `New`, `Serve`, the 5 tool handlers, result helpers |\n| `internal/mcpserver/server_suite_test.go` | create | ginkgo bootstrap + `gitRepo` helper |\n| `internal/mcpserver/server_test.go` | create | per-tool in-memory-transport tests |\n| `cmd/kref/commands.go` | modify | `newMCPCmd` |\n| `cmd/kref/main.go` | modify | register `mcp` in the setup group |\n| `README.md`, `CHANGELOG.md` | modify | docs |\n\n---\n\n## Task 1: dependency + server skeleton + `kref_remember` + `kref mcp` command\n\n**Files:** `go.mod`/`go.sum`, `internal/mcpserver/server.go`, `internal/mcpserver/server_suite_test.go`, `internal/mcpserver/server_test.go`, `cmd/kref/commands.go`, `cmd/kref/main.go`.\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Add the dependency**\n\n```bash\nGOTOOLCHAIN=auto go get github.com/modelcontextprotocol/go-sdk@v1.6.1\nGOTOOLCHAIN=auto go mod tidy\n```\nExpected: `go.mod` gains the require; `go.sum` updated. (If v1.6.1's core API differs from the \"Verified SDK API\" above — unlikely within 1.x — STOP and report.)\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Write the failing test** — create the suite bootstrap `internal/mcpserver/server_suite_test.go`:\n\n```go\npackage mcpserver_test\n\nimport (\n\t\"testing\"\n\n\tgogit \"github.com/go-git/go-git/v5\"\n\t. \"github.com/onsi/ginkgo/v2\"\n\t. \"github.com/onsi/gomega\"\n)\n\nfunc TestMCPServer(t *testing.T) {\n\tRegisterFailHandler(Fail)\n\tRunSpecs(t, \"MCP Server Suite\")\n}\n\nfunc gitRepo() string {\n\tGinkgoHelper()\n\tdir := GinkgoT().TempDir()\n\t_, err := gogit.PlainInit(dir, false)\n\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\treturn dir\n}\n```\n\nCreate `internal/mcpserver/server_test.go`:\n\n```go\npackage mcpserver_test\n\nimport (\n\t\"context\"\n\n\t. \"github.com/onsi/ginkgo/v2\"\n\t. \"github.com/onsi/gomega\"\n\n\t\"github.com/modelcontextprotocol/go-sdk/mcp\"\n\n\t\"github.com/riotbox/kref/internal/entry\"\n\t\"github.com/riotbox/kref/internal/mcpserver\"\n\t\"github.com/riotbox/kref/internal/store\"\n)\n\n// call connects an in-process client to a fresh server over an in-memory\n// transport, invokes one tool, and returns its result.\nfunc call(dir, tool string, args map[string]any) *mcp.CallToolResult {\n\tGinkgoHelper()\n\tctx := context.Background()\n\tclientT, serverT := mcp.NewInMemoryTransports()\n\tsrv := mcpserver.New(dir, \"test\")\n\tss, err := srv.Connect(ctx, serverT, nil)\n\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\tclient := mcp.NewClient(\u0026mcp.Implementation{Name: \"test\", Version: \"test\"}, nil)\n\tcs, err := client.Connect(ctx, clientT, nil)\n\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\tDeferCleanup(func() { _ = cs.Close(); ss.Wait() })\n\tres, err := cs.CallTool(ctx, \u0026mcp.CallToolParams{Name: tool, Arguments: args})\n\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\treturn res\n}\n\nfunc text(res *mcp.CallToolResult) string {\n\tGinkgoHelper()\n\tExpect(res.Content).NotTo(BeEmpty())\n\ttc, ok := res.Content[0].(*mcp.TextContent)\n\tExpect(ok).To(BeTrue())\n\treturn tc.Text\n}\n\nvar _ = Describe(\"kref_remember\", func() {\n\tIt(\"creates an entry the store can read back\", func() {\n\t\tdir := gitRepo()\n\t\ts, err := store.Init(dir, \"T\", \"t@e.com\")\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\t_ = s.Close()\n\n\t\tres := call(dir, \"kref_remember\", map[string]any{\n\t\t\t\"title\": \"Auth design\", \"body\": \"the body\", \"tier\": \"personal\", \"kind\": \"spec\",\n\t\t})\n\t\tExpect(res.IsError).To(BeFalse())\n\t\tExpect(text(res)).To(ContainSubstring(\"remembered\"))\n\n\t\ts2, err := store.Open(dir)\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tDeferCleanup(func() { _ = s2.Close() })\n\t\titems, err := s2.List(store.ListFilter{})\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\ttitles := make([]string, 0, len(items))\n\t\tfor _, it := range items {\n\t\t\ttitles = append(titles, it.Title)\n\t\t}\n\t\tExpect(titles).To(ContainElement(\"Auth design\"))\n\t})\n\n\tIt(\"returns a tool error for an invalid tier\", func() {\n\t\tdir := gitRepo()\n\t\ts, err := store.Init(dir, \"T\", \"t@e.com\")\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\t_ = s.Close()\n\t\tres := call(dir, \"kref_remember\", map[string]any{\"title\": \"X\", \"body\": \"y\", \"tier\": \"bogus\"})\n\t\tExpect(res.IsError).To(BeTrue())\n\t\tExpect(text(res)).To(ContainSubstring(\"tier\"))\n\t})\n})\n\nvar _ = Describe(\"placeholder for entry import\", func() {\n\tIt(\"keeps the entry import used\", func() { Expect(entry.TierPersonal).To(Equal(entry.Tier(\"personal\"))) })\n})\n```\n\n(The placeholder spec just keeps the `entry` import live until Task 2 uses it; delete it in Task 2.)\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Run, confirm FAIL** — `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto go test ./internal/mcpserver/...` → FAIL (no package `mcpserver`).\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Implement** — create `internal/mcpserver/server.go`:\n\n```go\n// Package mcpserver is a thin MCP adapter over internal/store. It exposes a\n// curated set of agentic tools; the store remains the only capability core.\npackage mcpserver\n\nimport (\n\t\"context\"\n\t\"fmt\"\n\n\t\"github.com/modelcontextprotocol/go-sdk/mcp\"\n\n\t\"github.com/riotbox/kref/internal/entry\"\n\t\"github.com/riotbox/kref/internal/store\"\n)\n\n// New builds the kref MCP server for a repository directory.\nfunc New(dir, version string) *mcp.Server {\n\ts := mcp.NewServer(\u0026mcp.Implementation{Name: \"kref\", Version: version}, nil)\n\tmcp.AddTool(s, \u0026mcp.Tool{\n\t\tName:        \"kref_remember\",\n\t\tDescription: \"Save a new knowledge-base entry (a memory). Returns its id.\",\n\t}, remember(dir))\n\treturn s\n}\n\n// Serve runs the kref MCP server over stdio until the host closes the connection.\nfunc Serve(ctx context.Context, dir, version string) error {\n\treturn New(dir, version).Run(ctx, \u0026mcp.StdioTransport{})\n}\n\nfunc textResult(s string) *mcp.CallToolResult {\n\treturn \u0026mcp.CallToolResult{Content: []mcp.Content{\u0026mcp.TextContent{Text: s}}}\n}\n\n// toolError reports a user-facing tool error (visible to the model, IsError=true)\n// rather than a protocol-level Go error.\nfunc toolError(format string, a ...any) *mcp.CallToolResult {\n\treturn \u0026mcp.CallToolResult{IsError: true, Content: []mcp.Content{\u0026mcp.TextContent{Text: fmt.Sprintf(format, a...)}}}\n}\n\nfunc parseTier(s string) (entry.Tier, bool) {\n\tswitch entry.Tier(s) {\n\tcase entry.TierPrivate, entry.TierPersonal, entry.TierShared:\n\t\treturn entry.Tier(s), true\n\tdefault:\n\t\treturn \"\", false\n\t}\n}\n\ntype rememberParams struct {\n\tKind   string   `json:\"kind\"`\n\tTitle  string   `json:\"title\"`\n\tBody   string   `json:\"body\"`\n\tTier   string   `json:\"tier\"`\n\tLabels []string `json:\"labels\"`\n}\n\nfunc remember(dir string) mcp.ToolHandlerFor[rememberParams, any] {\n\treturn func(ctx context.Context, _ *mcp.CallToolRequest, p rememberParams) (*mcp.CallToolResult, any, error) {\n\t\tst, err := store.Open(dir)\n\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\treturn nil, nil, err\n\t\t}\n\t\tdefer st.Close()\n\n\t\ttier := entry.TierPersonal\n\t\tif p.Tier != \"\" {\n\t\t\tt, ok := parseTier(p.Tier)\n\t\t\tif !ok {\n\t\t\t\treturn toolError(\"invalid tier %q (want private|personal|shared)\", p.Tier), nil, nil\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\ttier = t\n\t\t}\n\t\ttitle := p.Title\n\t\tif title == \"\" {\n\t\t\ttitle = entry.DeriveTitle(p.Body)\n\t\t}\n\t\tif title == \"\" {\n\t\t\treturn toolError(\"provide a title, or a body to derive one from\"), nil, nil\n\t\t}\n\t\tkind := p.Kind\n\t\tif kind == \"\" {\n\t\t\tkind = \"document\"\n\t\t}\n\t\tid, err := st.Add(tier, kind, title, p.Body)\n\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\treturn nil, nil, err\n\t\t}\n\t\tfor _, l := range p.Labels {\n\t\t\tif err := st.AddLabel(id, l); err != nil {\n\t\t\t\treturn nil, nil, err\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t}\n\t\t// MCP writes are agent-authored provenance.\n\t\tif err := st.RecordOrigin(id, \"mcp\", \"agent\", \"\", \"create\"); err != nil {\n\t\t\treturn nil, nil, err\n\t\t}\n\t\treturn textResult(\"remembered \" + id.String()), nil, nil\n\t}\n}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 5: Run, confirm PASS** — `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto go test ./internal/mcpserver/...`.\n\n- [ ] **Step 6: Add the `kref mcp` command** — in `cmd/kref/commands.go` add (and import `\"github.com/riotbox/kref/internal/mcpserver\"`):\n\n```go\nfunc newMCPCmd(dir *string) *cobra.Command {\n\treturn \u0026cobra.Command{\n\t\tUse:   \"mcp\",\n\t\tShort: \"Run an MCP server exposing kref tools over stdio\",\n\t\tRunE: func(cmd *cobra.Command, _ []string) error {\n\t\t\treturn mcpserver.Serve(cmd.Context(), *dir, Version)\n\t\t},\n\t}\n}\n```\n\nIn `cmd/kref/main.go`, register in the **setup** group (after `newHooksCmd`):\n\n```go\n\taddTo(\"setup\", newMCPCmd(\u0026dir))\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 7: Verify the CLI builds + the command is registered**\n\n```bash\nKREF_GITLEAKS=$(pwd)/bin/gitleaks GOTOOLCHAIN=auto go test ./cmd/kref/...\nGOTOOLCHAIN=auto go build ./...\n```\nExpected: PASS / clean build (the `mcp` command exists; existing CLI tests unaffected).\n\n- [ ] **Step 8: gofmt + commit**\n\n```bash\ngofmt -w internal/mcpserver/server.go internal/mcpserver/server_suite_test.go internal/mcpserver/server_test.go cmd/kref/commands.go cmd/kref/main.go\ngit add go.mod go.sum internal/mcpserver/ cmd/kref/commands.go cmd/kref/main.go\ngit commit -m \"feat(mcp): kref mcp stdio server + kref_remember tool\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 2: `kref_recall` + `kref_get`\n\n**Files:** Modify `internal/mcpserver/server.go`, `internal/mcpserver/server_test.go`.\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Write the failing tests** — in `server_test.go`, DELETE the \"placeholder for entry import\" Describe (Task 2 uses `entry`/`store` already) and append:\n\n```go\nvar _ = Describe(\"kref_recall and kref_get\", func() {\n\tIt(\"recalls entries by search and gets one by id\", func() {\n\t\tdir := gitRepo()\n\t\ts, err := store.Init(dir, \"T\", \"t@e.com\")\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tid, err := s.Add(entry.TierPersonal, \"spec\", \"Auth flow\", \"secret-free body about auth\")\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\t_ = s.Close()\n\n\t\trec := call(dir, \"kref_recall\", map[string]any{\"search\": \"auth\"})\n\t\tExpect(rec.IsError).To(BeFalse())\n\t\tExpect(text(rec)).To(ContainSubstring(\"Auth flow\"))\n\n\t\tgot := call(dir, \"kref_get\", map[string]any{\"id\": id.String()})\n\t\tExpect(got.IsError).To(BeFalse())\n\t\tExpect(text(got)).To(ContainSubstring(\"auth\"))\n\t})\n\n\tIt(\"kref_get returns a tool error for an unknown id\", func() {\n\t\tdir := gitRepo()\n\t\ts, err := store.Init(dir, \"T\", \"t@e.com\")\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\t_ = s.Close()\n\t\tgot := call(dir, \"kref_get\", map[string]any{\"id\": \"deadbeef\"})\n\t\tExpect(got.IsError).To(BeTrue())\n\t})\n})\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Run, confirm FAIL** — unknown tools `kref_recall`/`kref_get`.\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Implement** — register both in `New` (after the remember registration):\n\n```go\n\tmcp.AddTool(s, \u0026mcp.Tool{\n\t\tName:        \"kref_recall\",\n\t\tDescription: \"Find entries by a title/body substring and optional label/tier/kind filters.\",\n\t}, recall(dir))\n\tmcp.AddTool(s, \u0026mcp.Tool{\n\t\tName:        \"kref_get\",\n\t\tDescription: \"Read one entry in full by its id (or id prefix).\",\n\t}, get(dir))\n```\n\nAppend the handlers:\n\n```go\ntype recallParams struct {\n\tSearch string `json:\"search\"`\n\tLabel  string `json:\"label\"`\n\tTier   string `json:\"tier\"`\n\tKind   string `json:\"kind\"`\n}\n\nfunc recall(dir string) mcp.ToolHandlerFor[recallParams, any] {\n\treturn func(ctx context.Context, _ *mcp.CallToolRequest, p recallParams) (*mcp.CallToolResult, any, error) {\n\t\tst, err := store.Open(dir)\n\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\treturn nil, nil, err\n\t\t}\n\t\tdefer st.Close()\n\t\tf := store.ListFilter{Search: p.Search, Kind: p.Kind}\n\t\tif p.Label != \"\" {\n\t\t\tf.Labels = []string{p.Label}\n\t\t}\n\t\tif p.Tier != \"\" {\n\t\t\tt, ok := parseTier(p.Tier)\n\t\t\tif !ok {\n\t\t\t\treturn toolError(\"invalid tier %q (want private|personal|shared)\", p.Tier), nil, nil\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\tf.Tier = t\n\t\t}\n\t\titems, err := st.List(f)\n\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\treturn nil, nil, err\n\t\t}\n\t\tif len(items) == 0 {\n\t\t\treturn textResult(\"no matching entries\"), nil, nil\n\t\t}\n\t\tvar b strings.Builder\n\t\tfor _, it := range items {\n\t\t\tfmt.Fprintf(\u0026b, \"%s  [%s/%s]  %s\\n\", it.ID.String(), it.Tier, it.Status, it.Title)\n\t\t}\n\t\treturn textResult(b.String()), nil, nil\n\t}\n}\n\ntype getParams struct {\n\tID string `json:\"id\"`\n}\n\nfunc get(dir string) mcp.ToolHandlerFor[getParams, any